There should be an example in [Resolving a Location Reference](
https://developer.here.com/documentation/location-library/dev_guide/docs/location-referencing-tmc.html) section.

The resolver allows you to transform the `TMCLocationReference` into a `LinearLocation` containing internal HERE maps ids, which can be transformed to WKT like [`LineString`s](https://developer.here.com/documentation/location-library/api_reference_java/com/here/platform/location/core/geospatial/javadsl/LineString.html) using for instance the [`PropertyMaps.geometry`](https://developer.here.com/documentation/location-library/api_reference_java/com/here/platform/location/integration/optimizedmap/graph/javadsl/PropertyMaps.html) method, for which you can find more details in the [dev guide](https://developer.here.com/documentation/location-library/dev_guide/docs/high-level.html#property-maps).

As an example, you could do something like this:

```java
